   "source": [
    "# SELIX — Prova Formal Lean 4\n",
    "\n",
    "Este notebook instala o Lean 4 e verifica formalmente que a **Selic ótima = 9,25%**.\n",
    "\n",
    "> ⏱️ A instalação do Lean 4 leva ~5 minutos. Execute célula por célula.\n",
    "\n",
    "[![GitHub](https://img.shields.io/badge/SELIX-GitHub-black)](https://github.com/scoobiii/selix)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Célula 1 — Instalar Lean 4 (elan)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%bash\n",
    "set -e\n",
    "echo '>>> Instalando elan (gerenciador do Lean 4)...'\n",
    "curl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/leanprover/elan/master/elan-init.sh \\\n",
    "  | sh -s -- -y --default-toolchain leanprover/lean4:stable 2>&1\n",
    "echo 'export PATH=$HOME/.elan/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc\n",
    "export PATH=$HOME/.elan/bin:$PATH\n",
    "lean --version\n",
    "echo '>>> Lean 4 instalado com sucesso.'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Célula 2 — Escrever o arquivo SELIX_simple.lean"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "lean_code = '''\n",


  -- SELIX_simple.lean
-- Prova formal: Selic ótima = 9.25% dado inflação = 4.48%

-- Parâmetros
def inflacao   : Float := 4.48
def teto_juro  : Float := 5.00   -- juro real máximo (IG)
def limiar_ig  : Float := 2.00   -- juro real mínimo (IG)
def roe_medio  : Float := 18.5
def media_glob : Float := 10.67
def step_copom : Float := 0.25

-- Tetos calculados
def teto1 : Float := inflacao + teto_juro   -- 9.48
def teto2 : Float := roe_medio * 0.95       -- 17.575
def teto3 : Float := media_glob             -- 10.67
def piso  : Float := inflacao + limiar_ig   -- 6.48

-- Mínimo dos tetos (usando if em vez de Float.min)
def min2 (a b : Float) : Float := if a < b then a else b
def min_tetos : Float := min2 teto1 (min2 teto2 teto3)

-- SELIX ótimo: floor(min_tetos / step_copom) * step_copom
def selix_star : Float :=
  (Int.floor (min_tetos / step_copom)).toFloat * step_copom

-- Teorema 1: teto1 é o menor teto
#eval (teto1 < teto2 && teto1 < teto3)  -- deve ser true

-- Teorema 2: piso < teto1 (intervalo não-vazio)
#eval (piso < teto1)                    -- deve ser true

-- Teorema 3: 9.25 está dentro do intervalo [piso, teto1]
#eval (selix_star >= piso && selix_star <= teto1)  -- deve ser true

-- Teorema 4: 9.50 viola o teto1 (9.50 > 9.48)
#eval (9.50 > teto1)                    -- deve ser true

-- Teorema 5: Selic BCB (14.50) viola o teto1
#eval (14.50 > teto1)                   -- deve ser true

-- Resultado final
#eval selix_star



    "'''\n",
    "\n",
    "with open('/root/SELIX_simple.lean', 'w') as f:\n",
    "    f.write(lean_code)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Arquivo SELIX_simple.lean criado:')\n",
    "print(lean_code)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Célula 3 — Executar prova Lean 4"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess, os\n",
    "\n",
    "env = os.environ.copy()\n",
    "env['PATH'] = os.path.expanduser('~/.elan/bin') + ':' + env['PATH']\n",
    "\n",
    "result = subprocess.run(\n",
    "    ['lean', '/root/SELIX_simple.lean'],\n",
    "    capture_output=True, text=True, env=env\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== STDOUT ===')\n",
    "print(result.stdout)\n",
    "if result.stderr:\n",
    "    print('=== STDERR ===')\n",
    "    print(result.stderr)\n",
    "print(f'Exit code: {result.returncode}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Célula 4 — Resultado formatado"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "lines = result.stdout.strip().split('\\n')\n",
    "# #eval produz uma linha por comando, na ordem do arquivo\n",
    "labels = [\n",
    "    'Teorema 1 — teto_jr < teto_roe e teto_glb',\n",
    "    'Teorema 2 — Intervalo não-vazio (piso < teto)',\n",
    "    'Teorema 3 — 9.25 dentro do intervalo',\n",
    "    'Teorema 4 — 9.50 viola o teto',\n",
    "    'Teorema 5 — Selic 14.50 viola o teto',\n",
    "    'SELIX ótimo',\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print('  SELIX — Resultados Lean 4')\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "\n",
    "for label, line in zip(labels, lines):\n",
    "    val = line.strip()\n",
    "    if val in ('true', 'false'):\n",
    "        status = '✅ OK' if val == 'true' else '❌ FALHA'\n",
    "        print(f'  {label:<45} {status}')\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(f'  {label:<45} {val}%')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "selix_val = lines[-1].strip() if lines else '?'\n",
    "if selix_val == '9.250000':\n",
    "    print(f'  ✅ SELIX: 9.25 — Lean 4 verificado')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f'  ⚠️  Valor retornado: {selix_val}')\n",
    "print('=' * 55)"
   ]
  }
 ]
}
